'''Operation Texas Star''' was a military operation of the [[Vietnam War]] in the [[A Shau Valley]] and the mountains east of the valley from 1 April to 5 September 1970.

It aimed at regaining the initiative in the area. The operation culminated in the [[Battle of Fire Support Base Ripcord]], which ended with the evacuation of the base on July 23, 1970. 

Both the 101st Airborne Division and the ARVN 1st Infantry Division were involved in the operation.

